inn1.comm: again outside the off stump, good-length delivery seaming away, left alone
full-length delivery, around the off stump, driven to covers

nice delivery - it pitched around the middle and off stump line, full in length, and moved towardss the off stump, Dravid comes forward and places it in the extra cover region and they scramble through for a single
short of length, rising towards the hips, tucked away behind square leg.
full and on the off stump line, Dravid comes forward to push it back down the track
another good delivery, just about that off stump line, Dravid ends up playing ahead of his body and steers it point
pushed across Sehwag who drives on the up and it falls short of covers
ooh! full and wide outside the off stump and Sehwag attempts a square drive of his front foot, misses
Ah! full and wide again, and this time Sehwag throws the kitchen sink at it and ball flies off the outside edge over the slips!
hmm... pushed across again and Sehwag, despite moving his left foot across, fails to reach to the pitch of the ball and still has a go at it, doesn't connect and baugh collects it
Sehwag doesn't flirt this time! outside off again but Sehwag covers his off stump and allows it go to Baugh, the keeper.
on a length, around the off stump, steered to gully

oh ho! huge appeal for lbw. Full and it pitched around the middle stump line and Dravid gets his left across and has to end up playing around it a bit and the ball sneaks past his bat and his his pads but maybe, its going down the leg. Hawk eye might have shown it scrapping the leg stump... hmm...
beaten outside off! lovely delivery, shaping away after hitting the good length around the off stump and Dravid is beaten on the forward prod
good length delivery, on the middle stump line, Dravid leans forward and pushes it back down the pitch

Dravid is again beaten by the late movement! It pitched on a length, around the off stump and shapes away late and Dravid wants to play it on the up - maybe not a pitch for those kind of strokes, and gets a leading edge but the ball falls short of covers
beaten again! short of length delivery, in the channel outside the off stump and Dravid has a slash, misses and is beaten. Great start from Fidel
half-volley on the off stump and that high back lift of Sehwag comes down at a rapid pace and the ball screams past the left of mid-on.
short of length this time, on the off stump line, square driven to deep point
just outside the off stump, short of a length, steered past gully

gone! super catch! short of length and outside the off stump, Sehwag has a go at it again, threw his hands at it and the ball was ascending over Gayle, at covers, but Gayle times his jump perfectly to pouch the ball. The danger man Sehwag is gone!
a good length delivery on the off stump, coming in with the angle, Raina presses forward, bat and pad together and plays it quietly onto the off side
short of length outside the off stump, Raina gets back and across and steers it past gully
hmm ... should have been a wide down the leg side. Admittedly it didn't drift too wide down the leg but it was down the leg and usually umpires tend to give those
wide this time, full and well outside the off stump, Raina shapes to play and at the last minute lets it go. I dont think he would have reached it even if he had tried
short of length, on the off stump line, Raina hops back and punches it to covers.
similar length but this time on the leg and middle stump line, Raina tucks it off his hips, straight to square leg

Ah! a well-directed bouncer that had Raina hopping and skipping! Short and screaming throat high at 90 mph just on the off stump line. and Raina does well to avoid it. He jumps and sways to get outside the line. Good cricket all round
short of length, on the middle stump line, pushed to the on side
full and outside the off stump and Raina goes down on his knees and drives it covers. good looking shot but ...
ooh! almost dragged onto the stumps! Full and pushed across Dravid who ends up playing outside the line- maybe as he was trying to thrash it too hard and ball rolls onto the boots
good-length delivery, on the leg and middle stump line, Dravid pushes forward and plays it off his hips behind the square leg for a single
on the legs, short of length, and Raina glances it off his hips, down to Colleymore at fine leg
on the middle and leg stump line, Dravid comes forward and defends off the full face of the bat, back to the bowler
bit of bravado from Dravid! He comes down the track and Bradshaw drags back the length and Dravid is unable to force the ball
full and slanting across the left-hand batsman, driven elegantly to covers.
good ball, it pitched just outside the off stump and held its line and Raina punches it to mid-off
slightly shorter and rising about waist high, around the off stump line, Raina hops back and punches the ball down to the ground and it rolls over close on the off side
short of length and just outside the off stump, Raina doesn't get across, instead just hangs his bat away from his body and pushes it to cover
similar length but this one curves in after pitching on the middle stump, cramping Raina a bit who manages to push it out to short cover.
full and sucking Raina into a forward drive, a inside edge to fine leg results
short of length, on the leg and middle stump line, tucked to square-leg
this time Raina gets completely behind the line to a short of length delivery on the stumps and pushes it back down the track
similar delivery and again Raina gets behind the line to punch it back down the track
drifting down the leg and a wide called.
good-length delivery, just outside the off stump and Raina, this time plays away from his body, pushes at it and gets an outside edge,down to right of third man
short of length, on the legs, Raina gets inside the line and turns it down to fine leg.
full and well outside the off stump, Dravid gets his left foot across and then reaches out for the ball, well in front of his body, and steers it to gully
full length delivery, outside the off stump and shaping futher away, Dravid lets it go and has a look at the umpire, hoping for a wide but it wasn't so wide to be called

streaky four! short of length, outside the off stump and shaping away ever so slightly and Dravid pushes at it, away from his body, gets and edge and the ball flies through the non-existent second slip for a boundary
outside the off stump again but Dravid is not tempted this time, covers his off stump and lets it go
good length delivery outside the off stump and moving towards the slip, left alone
similar delivery and once again left alone. Colleymore is getting the ball to move off the seam here.

gone! short of length and a foot outside the offstump, Raina gets back and across and goes for a square-cut, rather a square-slash, gets the edge which flies fast  above head-high and to the right of Sarwan, at first slip, who pouches it safely. A very good catch and now India in trouble here.
short and climbing above waist high and Yuvraj pushes back and taps the ball down and it rolls over to the on side
tip and run! Yuvraj stands tall and punches it close to the off side and they take a quick single
short of a length and bouncing just outside the off stump, steered to gully.
short of length again, Bradshaw is getting bit of bounce here, and outside the off stump, left alone by Dravid
on the legs, Dravid hops back and tucks it behind square
short and wide outside outside the off stump, wasted delivery
another one! wider than the previous delivery and it's exercise time for Billy!
Collymore drifts onto to middle and leg, another wayward delivery, but atleast this one is legal, Dravid on the back-foot driving and he neatly clips it away past the fielder at mid-on
good length delivery, hint of swing, left alone outside the off stump
much better line and length, close to the off stump line and shaping in a touch, Yuvraj goes for the drive and ends up with an inside edge onto his pad
another decent delivery outside the off stump, angled across the left-hander, Yuvraj watches it all the way into the keeper's gloves
drifting down the leg side, Yuvraj gets well inside the line and nudges it down to fine leg for an easy single
Collymore struggling here with the left-right combination on, again drifts onto middle and leg and Dravid happily flicks it away well in front of square on the leg side
good length delivery, pitched on middle and off stump and angling across, Yuvraj stands tall on the back-foot and drives it away straight to the  fielder at cover, cautiously played

fuller length delivery on the stumps and Yuvraj drives it straight back to the bowler on the bounce, Bravo takes it cleanly and throws the ball up in the air, in a effort to fool the crowd and he succeeds big time!
shot! short and angling across, too short and too wide, Yuvraj leans back to get the momentum and the cuts shot makes perfect contact, ball rockets away to the backward point fence
defended outside the off stump, watchfully played
good length delivery, angling across, Yuvraj gets well forward and forces it away wide of the fielder at point
and as expected he is right on the money straightaway, Yuvraj gets forward and defends it straight back down the track to the mid-off region, just enough room and they scamper through for a single
angling across the right-hander, Dravid on the front-foot defending

short of a good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, Dravid shuffles across in an effort to work it away through midwicket but fails to make contact, ball clips the pad and rolls away behind the stumps
on the middle and off stump line, again impeccable line and length from Bradshaw, Dravid is made to defend and the ball rolls away towards cover

on the middle and leg stump line and Dravid neatly clips it away towards midwicket, brilliant diving stop from Bravo there cuts off a certain boundary, bit of a mix-up in the middle but the throw came in late and Dravid safely makes it back
good length delivery on the stumps, driven straight ot the man at mid-off - another good over from Bradshaw comes to an end
short of a good length delivery, pitched close to the off stump line and angling across, Yuvraj goes fishing but lucky for India he catches nothing
on the pads, tucked away towards square leg - no room for a single there
line and length delivery, no room offered and Yuvraj strokes it away towards point
another dot ball! on the middle and off stump line, no movement whatsoever, just the perfect line and length - Yuvraj watchfully punches it away towards cover
short of a good length delivery outside the off stump, ball stopped a bit after hitting the deck, Yuvraj reads it well and leaves it through to the keeper
swing and a miss outside the off stump, short and angling across, Yuvraj beaten by the extra bounce there
short of a good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, defended on the back-foot
another short delivery, angling across and that creates the width, Dravid leans back and cuts late, ball races away straight to the fielder at third man
on the middle and off stump line, hint of swing, Yuvraj gets right behind the line and defends it with a straight bat
on the middle and leg stump line, angled across, Yuvraj shuffles across a bit and tucks it away towards midwicket for a single

angling across, harmless delivery, Dravid stays back and steers it down to third man for a single - nicely opened the face of the bat at the point of impact to get it past the fielder at gully, excellent placement
driven straight back to the bowler
good length delivery, defended towards covers
drifting down the leg side, Dravid gets well inside the line and clips it away towards fine leg, runs hard and comfortably makes it back for the second

Collymore strikes! short of a good length delivery, pitched bit wide outside the off stump and slanting away ever-so-slightly, Dravid plays away from his body in an effort to run it down to third man, ball shapes away just enough to kiss the outside edge, Sarwan at second slip dives across to his right and takes a good low catch, India three down!
good length delivery, forced away towards cover
another good delivery from Collymore, Kaif on the front-foot defending

short and wide outside the off stump, horrible delivery to end the over, Kaif sizes it up quickly and cuts it away through cover point, got right on top of the bounce and rolled his wrist over to keep it down
left alone outside the off stump
driven down to mid-on
another extra! wayward delivery outside the off stump and umpire Doctrove is not happy with the width
follows it up with another wayward delivery down the leg side
back on track, good length delivery outside the off stump and Yuvraj drives it straight to the fielder at point
defended on the back-foot

short and wide outside the off stump, Yuvraj slashes hard at it and gets it away towards third man, dangerous second run called for and for the most part Yuvraj was struggling but in the end the fielder in the deep was bit slow and Yuvraj makes it back comfortably
driven hard but straight to the fielder at cover
good length delivery, defended watchfully
steered down to third man for an easy single, neatly played
good length delivery on the middle and leg stump line, Yuvraj takes his left-foot off the ground to get the momentum and drills it through midwicket, cracking shot
forced away towards cover point and they steal a single, well run
clipped away off the pads to the midwicket region for an easy single

good length delivery, cutting in a touch, Yuvraj plays down the wrong line and gets hit on the pad, loud appeal for lbw turned down, that looked close but Yuvraj got a big stride and he was hit on the front-pad
and the extras continues to mount, this one was again way down the leg side
driven away nicely through the gap between the cover fielders
good length delivery, angling across, ball stopped a bit and Kaif is early into the drive, ball goes in the air but well wide of the fielder at short cover, well bowled Bradshaw
eased away on the leg side
driven away towards cover
drifting down the leg side, ball clips the pad and rolls down to short fine leg
flicked away off the pads to long-leg for a brace, easy runs
short of a good length delivery, defended towards cover
good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, no room offered, Yuvraj gets a good stride in and defends it away towards short cover, Collymore moves across quickly and cuts off the single
slightly short and slanting away from the left-hander, Yuvraj plays inside the line and the ball goes through to the keeper
forced away towards mid-on
short of a good length delivery, close to the off stump line, punched off the back-foot and the ball finds the fielder at mid-off
maiden! tight delivery to end the over, Yuvraj leaves it through to the keeper
on the legs, turned to square-leg.
short of length, around the off stump line, Kaif comes forward and pushes it out to covers
superb bit of fielding by Bravo! Kaif flicks a length delivery to his right at square-leg but bravo moves quickly to make a sliding stop.
short of length, on the legs, Kaif tries to whip it to the on side,doesn't connect and they go through for a leg bye
on the legs, whipped away to fine-leg
length ball, outside the off stump, steered to point. That's the end of Bradshaw's quota of 10 overs.
floated on the middle stump line, Kaif comes down the track and drives it long-on
tossed just outsdie the off stump, Yuvraj comes forward and steers it to the left of backward point and they scramble through for a run
on the off stump line, cut to point
short, slow through the air and outside the off stump and Kaif latches onto the chance and cuts it past backward point
again slow through the air, Gayle is really taking the pace of the ball here, and Kaif this time pushes it onto the off side
fuller this time and driven to covers
Kaif is beaten on the forward prod and the ball rebounds off the pads on to the off side
tossed up fuller, and Kaif should have gone onto his front foot ,doesn't but manages to drive it to midwicket
full and outside the off stump, driven to long-off
beaten outside the off stump, short and turning away from the off stump line, Yuvraj attempts to cut but is beaten by the extra bounce
comes forward and punches it to left of long-on where Fidel makes the stop and hurls in a throw quickly and the Indians decide to settle for a single
glorious straight drive, supremely timed. Comes to the pitch of the ball and drives powerfully past the bowler and beats the diving long-on fielder
full-length delivery, driven out to long-on
comes down the track but Samuels drags back the length and Kaif has to be contended with pushing it back down the track
this time he punches it long-on for a single
slightly short and Yuvraj opens up by moving his right foot outside the leg stump and pulls it to the on side
on the leg and middle line, worked to the on side
fuller and just outside the off stump, driven inside-out past covers
flatter and pushed through a bit, Yuvraj stands tall to punch it down to long-off
That's the fifty partnership! driven to long-on
on the middle and off stump line, turning away, steered to short thirdman
short of length, on the leg and middle stump line, Yuvraj punches it down to long-on.
on a length, on the middle and leg stump line and holding its line, Yuvraj stands tall and punches it to mid-on
short of length, slanting across, Yuvraj stands tall again and plays a inside-out shot past the cover. 100 is up for India

oh ho! hit on the thighpads! Short of length, around the leg and middle stump line and it rears towards the hips and Yuvraj goes for his pull shot, but is beaten by the pace and the ball runs to the off side, past the slip
just short of a length, and outside the off stump, Kaif comes forward and drives on the up but straight to cover, no chance of a run

on a length, in that channel outside the off stump and it came in slightly with the angle and Kaif has a jab at it, ends up inside-edging onto his pads and the ball rolls close to off side and they hurry through for a single
on the leg and middle, tucked away to square-leg
tossed outside the off stump, bit of bounce as it curves in, pushed to the off side and they take a single
beaten outside the off stump as he shapes to cut a ball turning away from him
Take that! short, wide and bounces right about the perfect height for Yuvraj to have a go. He moves to the leg side and swats it through extra cover
driven out to long-off and Yuvraj will keep the strike

oh! beaten outside the off stump! It was full in length, and just outside the off stump and it kept low which surprised Yuvraj. He had shaped to drive it on the up and ends up with a waft outside the line
on a length, outside the off stump, punched to covers
full and probably a tad slower, Yuvraj waits on his front foot and drives it to covers
full again, 87.1 mph delivery, on the leg and middle stump line, Yuvraj comes forward to push it out to mid-on
full-length delivery on the middle and off stump line, pushed, ahead of his body, back down the track
full again, on the middle and leg stump line, Yuvraj leans forward, and punches it down the ground, to the right of mid-off and they hurry through for a single
full, yorker-length delivery on the leg and middle stump, dug out by Yuvraj and Smith makes the stop on his follow through
overpitched outside the off stump and yuvraj smashes it straight to Lara at covers. A foot either to left or to the right of Lara would have fetched Yuvraj a boundary but ...
full again and Yuvraj comes forward and drives it to the left of mid-on
short of length this time, outside the off stump and Kaif moves across and steers it to gully
full and square-driven by Kaif, but well stopped by Gayle who moved quickly to his right at point
a length delivery on the off stump line, driven to covers
full and on the off and middle stump line, Yuvraj stays beside the line of the ball and taps it gently to the off side and they hurry through for a quick single
super pull from Kaif! Short and on the middle stump, didn't bounce all that much - more evidence of the variable bounce on offer here but Kaif adjusts, swivels and plays a pull shot to perfection
ooh! almost a run-out! Kaif pushes a short of length delivery to the on side and Lara moves in quickly from midwicket and hurls in a throw and it just bounces inches over the stump.
on a length, and around the off and middle stump line, Kaif pushes forward, bat and pad together and punches it on the up to mid-off
slightly slower and a yorker length delivery, Kaif works it to Lara but this time they decide against taking a run.
steered down to third man for an easy single
good length delivery, defended outside the off stump
turned away off the pads to the square leg region

short of a good length delivery, pitched close to the off stump line and slanting away from the left-hander, line and length was just perfect, Yuvraj has a poke at it, like a stranger in a strange land searching for the mythical unicorn, ball moves away just enough to clip the outside edge, Baugh quickly moves across to his left and takes a good low catch - that's a big wicket!
played away well wide of the fielder at cover
quicker delivery to start with, played away towards cover
another good delivery, worked away cautiously, no room for a single there
eased away towards silly mid-off
on the stumps, worked away towards midwicket
fuller and quicker, driven straight back to the bowler - brialliant maiden from Smith
on the middle and off stump line, worked away towards midwicket
drifting down the leg side and that's rightly called a wide
good length delivery, cutting in from outside the off stump, Kaif waits for the ball and at the last moment flicks it away through midwicket for a brace
good length delivery, bit wide outside the off stump and Kaif punches it away through covers
fuller length delivery, close to the off stump line and Dhoni punches it away towards cover point
good length delivery outside the off stump, Kaif drives on the up and the ball goes wide of the fielder at cover, was in the air for a long time but well wide of the fielder
hint of swing, probably reversing away, defended watchfully
forced away towards cover
turned away towards midwicket
turned away off the pads to the deep midwicket
quicker delivery, defended watchfully, ball rolls away towards cover
driven in the air and straight back past the diving bowler, almost a catch
close to the off stump line and Dhoni has a go at it, ball clips the outside edge and races away towards third man
drifting down the leg side and all Kaif had to do was get bat on it, that he does beautifully and the ball rockets away to the fine leg fence
on the stumps, turned away well wide of the fielder at midwicket
good length delivery outside the off stump, Dhoni steps forward and drives it away through the gap between the cover fielders
played away on the leg side
good length delivery, pitched close to the off stump line and cutting in with the angle, Kaif leans forward and drives it down to long-on for a single
turning in from outside the off stump, turned away off the back-foot to the midwicket region
forced away straight to the fielder at gully
tossed up and turning in, driven away through cover point
excellent delivery, speared in on the off stump, fuller in length and Dhoni had to hurry, jams his bat down in time and digs it out straight back to the bowler
again driven away through cover point
turned away towards square leg
pitched up outside the off stump, driven away opening the face of the bat and the ball rolls away towards cover point
defended outside the off stump
turning in from outside the off stump, Kaif goes back and square drives it through cover point for yet another single
driven away on the leg side
good length delivery, Dhoni steps forwards and drives hard, thick outside edge and the ball races away to third man fence
turned away off the pads, gets it wide of the fielder at midwicket
better line and length, defended on the front-foot
driven down to long-on
worked away off the pads to the fine leg region, 8 runs coming off this over
turning in from outside the off stump, defended on the back-foot
slightly short and turning in, Kaif quickly goes back and cuts it away behind point
eased away towards short midwicket
again worked away on the leg side, this time they scamper through for a single
fuller length delivery, driven back to the bowler - not a well timed shot, ball came off the inner half of the bat
defended outside the off stump, Gayle runs through another over!
on the off stump line, pushed to left of covers
on the off stump line, again turning in slightly, pushed back down the track
slower through the air, outside the off stump, punched to covers
again slow through the air, Dhoni has to make all the pace by himself, and he ned up pushing it to the off side. Good intelligent bowling
on the leg and middle, turned to the on side.
full and driven back powerfully to Gayle
full, almost yorker length, on the leg and middle, worked to deep midwicket
yorker length delivery again! on the middle, dug out to covers
full again, worked past midwicket
much slower this time, Kaif waits and waits and turns it to squareleg
another real slow delivery, that hang in the air for what seemed an eternity, pushed to midwicket.
floated outside the off stumpm, Kaif comes forward and steers it past point and that's the fifty up for Kaif!
ooh almost a return catch! short of length and it came up very slow and Kaif is bit early into his stroke but it falls short of Samuels

Oh! a sitter dropped! tossed up, just short of a driveable length and once again Kaif is bit early into his drive and spoons up a simple catch to the right of Samuels who makes a mess of it! Amazing stuff!
pushed to right of midwicket
driven to midwicket and another miserly over comes to an end. India are made to crawl here
slow and on a yorker-length, driven back to the bowler
struggling to put away the ball on this track, another one pushed back down the pitch
yes sir! deja-vu, pushed back to Gayle!
on the leg and middle, punched to Lara at midwicket
Ah! finally a four! Short ball and on the leg and middle, Dhoni makes room by moving to his left and pulls it to deep midwicket fence.
pushed through, punched to covers
yorker length, on the middle and leg, dug out, back to the bowler
on the middle, full in length, pushed back to the bowler
wow! that one was real quick. fired in outside the off stump and Dhoni is late on his cut and is beaten
on the leg and middle, punched to the right of midwicket
four to end what has been a great miserly spell from Samuels. Kaif sweeps a full-length delivery  to long leg fence
77.9mph delivery, yorker length, punched back past (over) the bowler, on a bounce and they take a single
slow delivery, on the middle stump, right up there at the blockhole length, punched to mid-on
another blockhole delivery, on the middle and leg and that bottom-handed  twirl of the bat comes into the picture, and ball runs out to midwicket
another lovely yorker! squeezed out to square-leg
fascinating stuff, A yorker again and Dhoni, ever eager to come forward to have a go, only manages to squeeze it past cover
hmm.. Kaif has had enough of digging out yorkers, moves to his left and has a heave, gets a inside edge and it runs behind square-leg
Aha! lovely slower ball! just outside the off stump and Kaif waits to steer it to deep cover and they come back for two and make in time to beat the fine throw from Samuels.
Ah! a clever chip shot! Kaif moves outside the off stump and plays a pick-up paddle shot over square-leg

Gone! got him! Another Bravo special! A slow full-length delivery! Kaif is completely beaten and the ball squeezes past his waft to disturb the furniture. Yuvraj Singh can understand Kaif's pain... A similar delivery had got him in that exciting second match.
full and pushed across the left-handed batsman, pushed out to covers
slanted across, full in length, steered to thirdman
slower delivery again! 68.6 mph and outside the off stump, on a driveable length and Dhoni, who picks up the change in pace, waits and thrashes it over Bravo's head for a four! Take that!
on the off and middle stump line, steered to third man. Dhoni on strike now
77.6 mph yorker! dug out to midwicket and they hurry through for a single. Good cricket allround
low full-toss, driven powerfully back down the track,
Ah! Dhoni attempts to paddle a full delivery past the fine-leg, hits it left of short fineleg fielder and they take a run
driven powerfully to long-on.
wah! thrashed down the ground! driveable length delivery, outside the off stump, and Dhoni throws his hand at it and the ball screams to right of long-off fielder who had no chance.
bang! slower ball that went awry, ending up as a full toss, on the leg and Pathan swung it across to the deep midwicket fence

He gets his man! another slower one, just outside the off stump and Pathan shuffles across and tries to paddle it past the short fine leg fielder, who had been moved in just prior to this ball, but sends the ball straight to the waiting palms of Colleymore there!
hmm.... another slower ball from Bravo, full and it dips at the last minute and AGarkar pushes it to covers
This is fun! Another slower one from Bravo who has simply decided that's the way to go here and Agarkar is beaten outside the off stump!
omg! almost a run-out. Agarkar pushes it close to the off side and wants a run, Dhoni doesn't and Bravo runs in quickly, swoops on the ball and underarms a throw but misses the stumps.

Oh dear! Bravo gets another wicket courtesy his famous slower ball!  Released between his thumb and the forefinger and it loops in the air towards the off and middle stump and even as Agarkar's high back lift descends, the ball dips, grips the surface, turns in past the blade to take out the leg stump!
Clever little paddle sweep for four! full and drifting just outside the legstump, Dhonis shuffles across and tickles it past short fine-leg
And Dhoni this time picks the off side boundary! Fascinating stuff! he shuffles outside the leg stump and slices it over point! That powerful bottom hand again!
oh ho! Dhoni wants to sweep the mediumpacer now!  Doesn't connect and is rapped on the pads
yorker length delivery on the middle and leg, Dhoni digs it out to midwicket and there was a chance for run but Dhoni decides against it. Wants the strike! Here we go!

finally West Indies wilt under the pressure. Pulled to deepmidwicket and Dhoni turns blindly for the second run, Powar is rooted to his crease but Colleymore fails to stop the throw and Powar runs for the second run! Please scream like Bill Lawry here -- yes yes that famous It's all happening here!
Dhoni moves a bit towards his leg stump, Colleymore followed him and Dhoni ends up trying to heave it across the line, doesn't connect and they run through for a leg bye!

inn2.comm: a gentle loosener to start with, short and wide outside the off stump and Gayle straightaway goes after, cuts hard but the ball goes straight to the fielder at point, Pathan gets away with it
bit wide outside the off stump, shaping away from the left-hander, Gayle leaves it through to the keeper
another wide delivery outside the off stump, normally Gayle would have gone after it but not today.
again short and wide outside the off stump, in the slot for the cut but Gayle shoulders arms and the ball goes through to the keeper, this is interesting!
again left alone outside the off stump
pitched up in the slot outside the off stump, too tempting a delivery for Gayle and he drills it through the gap between mid-off and cover, sweetly timed and equally well placed

good length delivery outside the off stump and Samuels comes down hard on it, ball clips the outside edge and flies past the second slip, would have been an easy catch if a third slip was in place, Samuels too off the mark with a boundary
good length delivery, defended back to the bowler
better line and length, too close to go after it, defensively played back to the bowler
another good length delivery close to the off stump line, Samuels on the back-foot defending and the ball rolls away towards cover
short of a good length delivery, on the middle and off stump line, Samuels gets behind the line and defends it straight back along the carpet
beauty! good length delivery, drifting in with the arm and shaping away after hitting the deck, Samuels is sucked into the drive and the ball zips past the outside edge
on the middle and off stump line and Gayle thuds it straight to the fielder at mid-on, powerful shot but the placement was poor
too short and too wide outside the off stump, Gayle quickly picks up the length, rocks back and hammers it through the gap between the cover fielders, perfect timing and placement on this occasion
beamer outside the off stump, looked like it slipped out of Pathan's hand, he quickly apologises to the batsman but umpire Taufle pulls him over for reckless bowling
left alone outside the off stump
lovely line and length, defended towards cover
inside edge and the ball rolls down to fine leg, easy two
good length delivery, driven down to mid-on
punched wide of the fielder at cover, easy single
wide outside the off stump and Gayle flashes hard, ball clips the inside edge and goes to the keeper on the bounce
pitched up outside the off stump, left alone by Gayle
good length delivery, angling across the left-hander, Gayle leaves it through to the keeper
slightly short on the middle and off stump line, Gayle swings hard, a massive one-handed swing and the ball flies over the midwicket fence, amazing shot
good length delivery on the stumps, forced away towards cover
four more! good length delivery on the middle and leg stump line, drifting away, Samuels shuffles across, gets well inside the line and pulls it away to the fine leg fence, easy picking
Pathan struggling here under pressure, wayward delivery down the leg side and once again he is pulled over for reckless bowling
not again, another one down the leg side
much better line and length, defended on the front-foot

good length delivery on the middle and leg stump line, hint of in-wing, Samuels is comprehensively beaten, he plays down the wrong line and the ball hit him on the back pad, loud appeal and up goes the finger, that ball might have been sliding down the leg side but umpire Taufel was convinced that it would have clipped the leg stump
excellent delivery first up, Sarwan too is beaten by the late swing and the ball crashes into the pad, another loud appeal but umpire Taufel is unmoved
defended down on the off side, end of a successful over
left alone outside the off stump
short and wide outside the off stump and Gayle throws everything but the kitchen sink at it, one bounce and straight to the fielder at third man
on the middle and leg stump line, hint of swing, turned away off the back-foot and the ball rolls away behind the stumps on the leg side, bit of edge involved
good length delivery on the stumps, defended on the front-foot
short rising delivery, close to the off stump, Sarwan leans back - makes room and cuts it away through cover point for a brace
good length delivery on the stumps, cutting in, Sarwan defends on the back-foot but not cleanly, ball clips the inside edge, crashes into the pad and rolls away on the leg side
good length delivery outside the off stump, shaping away, Gayle plays inside the line

good length delivery, pitched close to the off stump line and shaping away, ball kept bit low after hitting the deck, Gayle had to hurry and the ball hits the bottom part of the bat but amazingly it rockets away to the long-off fence
good length delivery outside the off stump, defended on the back-foot
drifting down the leg side
good length delivery, shaping away from outside the off stump, defended on the back-foot
Pathan once again drifts down the leg side and Gayle helps it down to fine leg for a single

short of a good length delivery, pitched in-line and angling across, Sarwan leans back, makes enough room and glides it down to the third man fence, desperate dive from the fielder in the deep ends in vain - lovely touch shot that

Gayle continues on his merry way! slightly fuller and angling across, Gayle gets forward to the pitch of the delivery and clatters it down to the long-off fence, once bounce and over the rope she goes - the stands are buzzing with activity, they are already sensing a West Indian victory here!
left alone outside the off stump
swing and a miss outside the off stump, that was a needless shot but that's the way he plays!

short ball on the stumps and Gayle happily pulls it away through midwicket, Powar gives chases and it looked like he had it covered but in the end he messes up an easy pick-up and the ball trickles over the fence
better line and length, Gayle leaves it through to the keeper
bit wide outside the off stump and angling away, no shot offered
good length delivery outside the off stump, played away towards covers

Agarkar strikes back for India! rank short ball, had six written all over it, for a moment Sarwan might have thought that he was dreaming, suddenly the alarm-bell goes off and he goes for the pull, a nothing shot in the end - ball clips the top edge and balloons up towards square leg, Sehwag calls for it early and nicely settles under it
left alone outside the off stump
line and length delivery outside the off stump, angling away, no shot offered
on the middle and leg stump line, turned away towards midwicket
good delivery to end the over, Lara leaves it through to the keeper
driven straight to the fielder at mid-on

good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, Gayle on the back-foot defending, ball shapes away just enough to kiss the outside edge but falls well short of the keeper, Sreesanth appeals for an lbw but the umpire is not interested
good length delivery on the stumps, defended
wicket to wicket delivery, played away towards midwicket
good length delivery, angling across, Gayle moves back and across and comes down hard on it and the ball goes straight to the fielder at cover
back-to-back maidens! short and wide outside the off stump, Gayle cuts hard but fails to make contact
ooh! swing and a miss! Lara goes back and across and has a go at a full-length delivery outside the off stump
dug in short and it rose above waist high, on the leg and middle stump line and a surprised Lara hops back to jab it to midwicket
short of a length delivery, on the middle stump line, Lara hops back and across, gets outside the line, and tucks it away to midwicket
that whiplash cover drive is out! Full and pushed across him, but Lara moves towards the ball and unfurls his cover drive
short of length and it pitched on the leg stump and shaped away to the legs of Lara who tries to glance, misses and the ball runs off his thigh pad to fine-lef fence
full and slanted across Lara, well outside the off stump but Lara tries to reach for it and drive it past covers, doesn't time well and the ball rolls to cover&
almost a catch! falls just short of Powar at mid-off. Full and in the slot, Gayle drives it on the up ...
beaten outside the off stump! beaten by the lack of bounce. Variable bounce coming into play here. Gayle ends up playing outside the line
full-length delivery, outside the off stump, slanting away, Gayle goes forward and drives it out to covers
good ball- yorker length, on the off stump line, Gayle jabs at it and the inside edge takes the ball close to the off side and they hurry through for a quick single
good slower ball, 74.2mph. on the leg and middle stump line, Lara comes forward, takes his top hand out of the bathandle and plays it quietly onto the off side
delivered from wide of the crease, full and slanting away, driven out to cover
short of length, on the middle stump and shaping in slightly and Gayle, although cramped a bit, manages to turn it past midwicket for a single
lovely ball, yorker length, on the middle stump, Lara shuffles across and digs it across the line to midwicket
good-length delivery, just outside the off stump and Lara, on the shuffle, attempts to drive it on the up, doesn't connect well and gets a inside edge on to the leg side
a length delivery, on the middle stump line, Lara goes back and across and dead bats it away to the on side
much fuller this time, on the leg and middle, whipped past midwicket
lovely slower ball, on the middle stump, full in length, a initially surprised Lara manages to get his bat down in time and the ball runs to fine leg, off the inside edge
full and on the leg and middle stump, Lara moves forward and across and chips it over midwicket for a boundary.
short of length and well outside the off stump, Lara covers the stumps and lets it go to Dhoni
short of driveable length, around the off stump, coming in with the angle, Lara leans forward and jabs it down to the on side
similar length, pitched on the same spot, outside the off stump but this time it shaped away from Lara, who moved forward, covered his off stump and let it go
wide outside the off stump, and called a wide
on a length, around the off stump line, Lara comes forward, doesn't quite manage to reach upto the pitch of the ball and jabs it down to square-leg
attempted yorker turns out as a low full-toss and Lara, on the front foot, drives it back down the pitch.
four straightup after the break! Gayle shifts his weight back and drives a short of length delivery, on the up past covers
shuffles across to a short of length delivery on the middle and off stump line and jabs it down on to the on side
outside the off stump, left alone
drifting down the leg side, and a wide called. Agarkar shakes his head in disappointment at himself and goes back to top of his mark
pushed across Gayle who covers his off stump and shoulders arms
full and on the off and middle stump line, Gayle leans forward and offers the full face of the bat in defence and the ball rolls out to point
short of length, on the off stump, Gayle, as his wont, stays where he is and punches it to point
tossed up on the off stump line, defended back watchfully
well-flighted delivery, on the leg and middle and turning past Lara, who comes forward and pushes it to off side
fuller and on the legs, Lara tries to whip it away, doesn't connect and is rapped on the pads
tossed up, outside the off stump, driven to cover
on the leg and middle stump line, turning away and Lara dead bats it to the of side
pitched on the middle and turning towards slips, Lara comes forward and steers it to point
Almost caught by Dhoni! slower ball that bounced high and leaving Gayle who pushes at it with a open face and the ball falls just short of a diving Dhoni
short of length, angling across, left alone by Gayle
fuller this time, on the off and middle stump line, Gayle comes forward and punches it to covers
another good line and length delivery, pitched on the middle stump line and shaping away towards the off stump, Gayle covers the line and pushes it back down the pitch
pitched outside the leg stump and came in towards the leg, Gayle shuffles, and turns it past square-leg
short and rising waist high on the leg and middle stump line, Lara hops back and across, gets outside the line and works it to long-leg
tossed up, dragging Lara out, pushed out to point
well-flighted delivery just outside the off stump, inviting him to drive which he successfully does, out to long-off
flatter and coming in from outside the leg stump and pushed back down the track
lovely arm ball! pitched on the leg and middle stump and hurried on straight and Gayle manages to jab it down in time
much slower this time, pitched on the leg and middle, pulled to deep midwicket
pitched outside the leg and even though it turned in, it stayed outside the leg stump and a wide called
tossed on the leg and middle stump line, lara tries to play an inside out cover drive, doesn't time it well and gets a inside edge which takes the ball to the on side
on the off and middle, Gayle gets behind the line and pushes it to covers
short of length, on the off stump line, Gayle backs away a bit, towards the leg stump, and punches it to right of covers
attempted yorker turns into a low full toss, a surprised Lara takes his top hand out of the bat-handle and turns it to midwicket
fuller and on the leg and middle stump line, Lara whips it off his stumps, past square leg and runs hard for two
nice slower ball, full and it looped on the off stump and Lara, on the drive, stops and plays it one-handed to covers
short of length, on the middle stump line, Lara gets back and across and offers the full face in defense
on that leg and middle stump line and turning away from Gayle, who presses forward and steers it past slips
slightly shorter this time and it pitched on the middle and turning away, Gayle goes to his back foot to punch it to covers
on the middle and off, turning past Gayle who lets it go to Dhoni
brave leave there from Gayle! it pitched on the middle stump and turned past the off stump, Gayle doesn't get his body in line, instead just lets it go.
on the legs, tucked away behind squareleg
on the legs, flicked past the square-leg for a single

short and drifting away from the left-hander, Lara waits for it and at the last moment cuts it away towards short third man, Yuvraj there fails to stop it cleanly and the batsmen scamper through for a single
cut away to deep point, easy single
comes down the track to the pitch of the delivery and drives it away to deep cover, excellent use of the feet
short and wide outside the off stump, was there to be hit but Gayle fails to get it past Kaif at cover
on the stumps, Gayle fails to make contact and the ball rolls away off the pad
fuller length delivery, defended down on the off side
comes down the track, even before the ball is bowled, Harbhajan drags it back a bit troubling Lara with the length, but he adjusts well and defends it away towards cover
defended outside the off stump
quicker delivery, turned away off the pads to deep backward square leg region
bit of width offered outside the off stump and Gayle cuts it away well in front of point
tossed up on the stumps, Lara goes for the sweep and connects well, easy single down to fine leg
on the middle and leg stump line, nothing delivery, Gayle stays back and drives it away through midwicket, fumble is the deep gives away an extra run
tossed up on the leg stump line, Lara comes down the track, gets close to the ball and turns it away well in front of square
short ball, turning across, Gayle rocks back and pulls it away through the gap between mid-off and midwicket, gets it wide of the fielder in the deep and they comfortably come back for the second

tossed up on the middle and off stump line, drifting away, Gayle comes down the track and swings hard, looking to clear the man at long-off, gets the height but not the distance and Agarkar in the deep judges it to perfection, Powar with the much needed breakthrough - West Indies three down.
defended on the front-foot
left alone outside the off stump
tossed up and turning across, defended watchfully
left alone outside the off stump, excellent line and length from Harby
fraction short and Lara cuts it away off the back-foot to deep point for a single
tossed up and turning in, worked away straight to the fielder at short leg
good length delivery, turning in from outside the off stump, Bravo gets right behind the line and defends it with a straight bat
fuller length delivery, Bravo leans well forward and drives it down to long-on for a single
quicker delivery, the one that goes straight on, Bravo pushes forward then quickly leans back and cuts hard, ball clips the bottom edge and goes past the keeper
defended down on the leg side
played away towards covers

on the middle and leg stump line, genuine off-spinner, Bravo comes forward looking to chip it away towards midwicket but the shot is not timed well enough the ball steeples off the leading edge, luckily for him the ball lands safely behind square
defended back to the bowler
swept away to fine leg for a single
turned away towards square leg, bit of a mix-up going for the single and in the end they make it across comfortably
turned away straight to the fielder at midwicket
tossed up outside the off stump, turning away sharply, Lara reads it well and leaves it through to the keeper
well flighted delivery outside the off stump, in the slot and Lara drives it down to long-off for a single, 100 comes up for West Indies and that gets the crowd going
turning in from wide outside the off stump, Bravo stands his ground and strokes it away towards point
turn and bounce, Bravo on the back-foot defending, gets beaten by a long way and gets hit high on the pad

flatter delivery outside the off stump, bowled from round the stumps, Lara dances down the track and swings hard, eyeing the cover fence, ball clips the outside edge and flies over the fielder at point, lucky runs
defended towards point
quicker delivery, defended back to the bowler
another line and length delivery, again defended back to the bowler
gets it right this time! tossed up outside the off stump, Lara chips down the track to the pitch of the delivery and drives it over the fielder at cover, clean hit
drifting down the leg side, ball clips the pad and rolls down to short fine leg
fuller and on the pads, turned away straight to Sehwag at midwicket, missed out there on some easy runs
on the stumps and turning away, Lara comes down the track but fails to get to the pitch of the delivery and in the end he just taps it away on the off side
driven wide of the fielder at mid-on
on the middle and leg stump line, not much turn there, Lara quickly goes down on one knee and slogs it away to deep backward square leg
quicker delivery, this one gripped the surface and turned in sharply, Bravo is beaten by the extra turn, ball clips the pad and pops up on the leg side, half-hearted appeal for lbw turned down
pitched outside the off stump and turning away, Lara leaves it through to the keeper

comes down the track, didn't quite get to the pitch of the delivery but he nicely opens the face of the bat and drives it away well in front of point, then he takes on Sehwag running in from the deep and makes it across safely for the second run, excellent cricket this from the West Indian captain
driven straight to the fielder at cover, good shot for no runs
down the leg side, that's a clear wide
comes down the track and drives it away right into the hole between mid-on and midwicket, Lara using his feet to good use here
nudged away to fine leg for an easy single
flat delivery, pitched outside the off stump and turning across, Lara waits on the back-foot and at the last moment taps it down to third man
tossed up on the stumps, bit too full and Bravo slogs it away to the midwicket fence, nicely going down on one knee as he played it, didn't even bother to keep it down, confident looking shot that
punched off the back-foot and the ball races away towards cover, Sehwag messes it up and two more runs are added to the total
drifting down the leg side, easy picking but Bravo fails to make contact, Harbhajan gets away with it
defended on the front-foot
swept away to fine leg for an easy single
tossed up and turning away, defended watchfully
on the leg and middle, tucked away behind square-leg for a single. Lara on strike now
he dances down the track again but Powar drags back the length and Lara has to push it back down the track
this time he reaches upto the pitch of the ball and drives to long-off
tossed up outside the off stump, Bravo gets across and whips it to midwicket
lovely shot! short and pitched outside the off stump, turning in, Bravo waits, moves to the leg stump and punches it past covers
tossed on the off stump line, swept to long-leg
It pitched outside the leg stump and turned in, Bravo is squared up a bit and it tickles off the outside edge to the off side
driven past Rahul Dravid at midwicket, who fumbles and they take a easy run.
delighful late cut! short and outside the off stump, Lara gets back and across, waits and then cuts it late to third man fence
tossed on the off stump, driven to squareleg
on the leg and middle stump line, Bravo pushes at it, and gets an inside edge which takes the ball to square-leg and they hurry through for a single
well-flighted delivery on the off stump, driven to the off side. doesn't time it well though
Another fumble! this time by Sreesanth at point. Bravo cuts a short of a length delivery to right of him
on the leg and middle, Bravo moves back and tucks it behind square-leg
fifty of the partnership is up! tossed on the middle stump, turning away but Lara dances down the track and whips it, in front of his body, against the spin to deepmidwicket fence
comes down the track again, but Powar holds back the length and Lara has to contend himself with pushing it back down the pitch.
from around the wickets, comes in with the arm, on the off stump, pushed back down the track
pitched on the leg and middle and turns towards middle stump, pushed out to the on side
on the middle and turning towards slip, short in length, Bravo goes back and swats it acros the line to right of midwicket
comes forward, bat and pad together and offers the dead bat in defense
on the off and middle stump line, Lara comes forward and opens the face of the bat at the last minute to steer it to gully region
tip and run! pushed close to the off side, to backward point area and they hurry through for a quick single
short of length, just outside the off stump, out comes Bravo and steers it to third man fence
lovely ball and very well left by Lara. It was on a length, and just outside the off stump and holding its line, Lara initially shapes to play but at the last minute lets it go
short of length again but this time closer to the off stump, Lara hops back, and steers it to thirdman fence
on the middle stump, short of length, Bravo gets across, inside the line and whips it off his hips to long-leg

on a length, on the leg and middle stump line, Lara this time doesn't get across, waits, stays beside the line, and with soft hands pushes it close on the off side and they hurry through for a quick single
short and rising waist high, on the middle and leg stump line, Bravo hops back, jumps to play the pull - calypso style- down to long-leg
on the leg and middle, driven to wide mid-on
fabulous shot to reach his fifty! dances down the track, but still finds himself short of the ball, and whips it across and over midwicket!
comes down the track again but Harbhajan pushes this one through and Lara defends it watchfully
full and pushed through, on the middle stump line, whipped across to backward square-leg
on the leg and middle stump line, swept over square-leg
appeal for lbw but turned down. It pitched just outside the off stump and Bravo is rapped on his pads as he tries to sweep it away but the ball was clearly heading down the leg side
on a length, and slanting across, Lara tries to slash it square, mistimes it and the inside edge takes the ball close onto the off side
full and on the off stump line, Lara comes forward and punch-drives it past cover
delivered from wide of the crease, on the legs, Bravo gets inside the line and whips it behind square-leg and they run really hard
on a length, just outside the off stump and holding its line, Bravo drives it on the up to mid-off
short of driveable length, on the off stump line and Bravo reaches out and ends up trying to whip it across the line, gets an outside edge and it flies through gully.

on the leg and middle stump line, Bravo comes forward and across and whips it to midwicket. Agarkar gets rapped on the knees as he goes down to make the stop and he limps off the field now!  Crucial blow, hopefully he will recover in time, as he has four overs in his kitty.
on the legs, whipped to Sehwag at midwicket
nice delivery, that pitched on the leg and turned towards slips, Lara comes forward, adjusts to the spin and pushes it with soft hands, out to the off side
Wah! great shot! tossed on the leg stump line, just outside in fact and Lara waltzes down the track, to the pitch of the ball and plays a pick-up shot over midwicket!
super shot! tossed on the leg and middle stump line and Lara just reaches out, thrusts his right foot forward and whips it over square-leg. Lara on fire here!
Lara dances down the track again, to a ball pitching just outside the off stump, and lofts it over long-on, for a superb six!  Lara has tamed Harbhajan here!
pushed through flat and quicker, cut straight to backward point
a length ball, just outside the off stump, Bravo leans forward and whips it across, past the bowler!
driven to covers
full and pushed across, Lara comes forward and attempts to go for his whiplash cover drive, doesn't time it well, gets an inside edge and the ball runs down back to the bowler
on the leg and middle stump line, Lara thrusts his right foot across and whips it across to the square-leg region
a length ball, outside the off stump but Bravo walks across to whip it behind square leg!
short of length, on the middle stump line and Bravo once again tries to whip it across, doesn't connect properly and Sreesanth rushes across to the short-leg area to make the stop
comes down the track again, and Powar holds back the length and Lara adjusts to push it to the off side

gone! Lara falls! A wonderful innings comes to an end. Powar tosses one up, on the leg and middle stump, Lara is again down the track and tries to hoick it up and over long-on, gets a leading top edge to mid-off.
tossed on the off stump and it turns in sharply and Bravo goes back rather than forward and is cramped for room but manages to push it to point
outside the off stump, short in length, and Bravo waits on his back foot and cuts it past Dravid at slips

almost a catch! a tough chance. Bravo backs away to the leg side and cuts, a short of length delivery on his stumps, in the air and Sehwag, at covers, jumps up and stretches out his right hand but only manages to get a finger touch..
good length delivery outside the off stump, good delivery to start with, Hinds on the front-foot defending
driven straight back to the bowler
good length delivery, Hinds drives it straight to the fielder at mid-off
again driven back to the bowler, Hind taking his time here
on the middle and leg stump line, driven straight to the fielder at mid-on
good length delivery outside the off stump, Hinds unleashes himself into the drive and the ball rockets away off the middle of the bat, fielder at cover had no chance whatsoever
they are doing it calypso style! tossed up on the middle and off stump line, Bravo dances down the track to the pitch of the delivery and murders it straight back over the bowler's head
swept away neatly to fine leg for a brace, it's getting all too easy out there and they are doing it in style!

four more! slightly short and turning in from outside the off stump, Bravo leans back, makes room and drills it past the cover fielder, no stopping that, 12 runs from four ball - just 14 needed now, at this rate it won't be long
goes for the seep but fails to connect, ball clips the pad and pops up on the leg side
comes down the track and tries to sweep, but fails to make contact
on the middle and leg stump line, driven straight to the fielder at mid-on
on the middle and off stump line, Hinds watchfully drives it down to mid-off
yorker, way outside the off stump, Hinds flashes hard but fails to make contact
fulltoss outside the off stump, Hinds stands his ground and clatters it through the gap between the cover fielder, easy picking, an avalanche of cheers accompanies the ball to the fence
defended back to the bowler
good length delivery outside the off stump, driven down to long-off for an easy single, just 10 more needed now
turned away towards square leg
flat delivery, turning in from wide outside the off stump, Bravo goes right back, using the crease to maximum advantage and taps it down to third man for an easy single
driven wide of the cover fielder, easy single
short delivery, again turning in from outside the off stump, this time Bravo goes right back and cuts it away through cover point, three more added
drifting down the leg side, Raina doing his bit
driven straight to the fielder at cover

there it is! tossed up on the stumps, bowled from round the wickets, Hinds quickly goes down on one knee and slogs it away to the midwicket fence - crowd goes wild, West Indies win by 6 wickets and they take the series 3-1.
